1.4
log
@scrub gone
@
text
@block
block return
block return-rst proto tcp
pass
pass in no state
pass out no state
pass all no state
block in all
block out all
block from any to any
pass in from any to any
pass out from any to any
block on lo0
pass on lo0 all
block on lo0 from any to any
pass proto tcp flags S/SA
pass proto udp keep state
pass in proto udp all keep state
pass out proto udp from any to any keep state
pass out on lo0 proto tcp from any to any port 25 keep state
@


1.3
log
@Handle default 'flags S/SA keep state', 'no state' and 'flags any'.
@
text
@a0 6
scrub
scrub all
scrub in
scrub out
scrub in all
scrub from any to any
@


1.2
log
@fromto is optional now, "from any to any" equals "all" equals omitted.
A single rule "block" is not valid, and does the same as "block in all,
block out all".
@
text
@d11 3
a13 3
pass in
pass out
pass all
@


1.1
log
@Direction (in/out) is now optional in filter rules, 'block all' is valid,
for instance. Add a regress test for those.
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
#scrub
d3 2
a4 2
#scrub in
#scrub out
d7 6
a12 6
#block
#block return
#block return-rst proto tcp
#pass
#pass in
#pass out
d19 1
a19 1
#block on lo0
d22 2
a23 2
#pass proto tcp flags S/SA
#pass proto udp keep state
@

